This paper is about unsupervised learning of generative models, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on generative adversarial networks (GANs), variational autoencoders, and flow-based models, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) applications. The paper also discusses the use of deep invertible transformations, which is a technique that is relevant to neural networks (cs.NE) and statistical learning (cs.SD). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.SD, in that order.
